12. B6ii: a restless Celtic tribe with an interesting history. The name occurs, as one already familiar, as early as Plaut. Cnpt. 888. According to Liv. V. 35, 2, they, among others, about the 4th century Β,0., left their Gallie homes and overran Etruria and Umbria. They were not finally defeated till 193 Bs. Another branch had remained in their ancestral territory about the Hercynian forest, where, in the 2d century, they successfully resisted the Cimbri. Shortly before Caesar's arrival, they crossed over to Noricum (cp. B. G. I. 5, 3), 32‚000 of them accompanying the Helvetii into Gaul.
